sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    box rgb(240,240,240) External
        participant User as User / Platform Operator
    end

    box rgb(255,243,224) Kubernetes Control Plane
        participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        participant Webhook as KubeRay Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    end

    box rgb(224,242,241) KubeRay Operator
        participant RCC as RayCluster Controller
        participant AuthC as Authentication Controller
        participant NPC as NetworkPolicy Controller
        participant MTLSC as mTLS Controller
        participant RJC as RayJob Controller
        participant RSC as RayService Controller
    end

    box rgb(232,245,233) Ray Cluster
        participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        participant Dashboard as Ray Dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
        participant Serve as Ray HTTP Proxy<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    end

    box rgb(243,229,245) External Services
        participant CertMgr as cert-manager
        participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    end

    Note over User, Gateway: Flow 1: RayCluster Lifecycle (RHOAI/OpenShift)

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutating admission (9443/TCP HTTPS)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Enforces odh.ray.io/secure-trusted-network=true,<br/>disables enableIngress
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validating admission (9443/TCP HTTPS)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validates name format + worker group uniqueness

    K8sAPI->>RCC: RayCluster event (watch)
    RCC->>K8sAPI: Create head Pod, Services (443/TCP HTTPS)
    K8sAPI->>AuthC: RayCluster event (watch)
    AuthC->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute (platform ns),<br/>ReferenceGrant, ConfigMap, SA (443/TCP HTTPS)
    K8sAPI->>NPC: RayCluster event (watch)
    NPC->>K8sAPI: Create head + worker NetworkPolicies (443/TCP HTTPS)
    K8sAPI->>MTLSC: RayCluster event (watch)
    MTLSC->>CertMgr: Create Issuers + Certificates (443/TCP HTTPS)
    CertMgr-->>MTLSC: TLS secrets provisioned

    RCC->>K8sAPI: Create worker Pods (443/TCP HTTPS)

    User->>Gateway: Access Ray Dashboard<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.3, OIDC/OAuth
    Gateway->>KRBP: HTTPRoute → kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview (services/get)
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Authorized
    KRBP->>Dashboard: Proxy to localhost:8265<br/>HTTP plaintext

    Note over User, Gateway: Flow 2: RayJob Submission (K8sJobMode)

    User->>K8sAPI: Create RayJob CR
    K8sAPI->>RJC: RayJob event (watch)
    RJC->>K8sAPI: Create transient RayCluster (443/TCP HTTPS)
    RJC->>K8sAPI: Create K8s Job submitter pod (443/TCP HTTPS)
    Note over RJC, Dashboard: K8s Job submitter Pod
    RJC->>Dashboard: SubmitJob (8265/TCP HTTP, no auth)
    RJC->>Dashboard: GetJobInfo / StopJob (8265/TCP HTTP)
    Dashboard-->>RJC: Job status response

    Note over User, Gateway: Flow 3: RayService Zero-Downtime Upgrade

    User->>K8sAPI: Update RayService CR
    K8sAPI->>RSC: RayService event (watch)
    RSC->>K8sAPI: Create pending RayCluster (443/TCP HTTPS)
    RSC->>Dashboard: UpdateDeployments (8265/TCP HTTP)
    RSC->>Dashboard: GetMultiApplicationStatus (8265/TCP HTTP)
    RSC->>Serve: CheckProxyActorHealth (8000/TCP HTTP)
    Serve-->>RSC: Health OK
    RSC->>K8sAPI: Switch Services to pending cluster,<br/>promote pending → active (443/TCP HTTPS)
